        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): harden Windows node pairing and approvals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve existing untagged device tokens for same-key metadata refresh approvals when the token was already valid before approval\n- keep rotating for scope expansion, public-key repair, stale baseline tokens, revoked/issuer-tagged tokens, incompatible role/scopes, and malformed persisted token entries\n- make devices/nodes/gateway CLI RPC helpers use the direct local gateway-client admin path for explicit loopback token/password auth, avoiding stale paired CLI identity/scope traps\n- make `approvals get --node` tolerate host-native Windows exec policy payloads instead of crashing on the local approvals-file shape\n- harden stable Windows node identity/event routing, node approval RPC authz, explicit loopback shared-token probing, and pending node-list presentation\n\n## Draft Snapshot\nCurrent pushed draft head: `19f504dc88bb2fcd7b19eb43fe2529c1474752a2`.\n\nThis branch is rebased onto current `main` and GitHub reports it as mergeable. The final rebase had one import-only conflict in `src/gateway/node-registry.ts`; resolution kept the new package number-coercion import plus this branch's node identity import.\n\n## Proof So Far\n- Focused pairing/auth proof after the earlier rebase passed: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/program.nodes-basic.e2e.test.ts src/gateway/node-catalog.test.ts src/gateway/node-command-policy.test.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-pairing-authz.test.ts src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts src/infra/node-pairing.test.ts src/infra/exec-approvals.test.ts src/cli/exec-approvals-cli.test.ts`.\n- Gateway call mock regression tests passed after the autoreview fix: 8 files / 201 tests.\n- Direct loopback gateway auth regression tests and targeted oxlint passed for the SecretRef/shared-token fix.\n- Earlier Azure pond proof on prior draft head `aec31cb62ba9e69314ab5a7b84d4049a38a10eea`: Linux gateway plus two signed Windows `v0.6.0-alpha.14` nodes connected, pairing converged, pending=0, paired=2, commandlessPaired=0, exec allow/deny worked, and safe feature smoke covered `system.which`, `device.info`, `device.status`, `camera.list`, and `screen.snapshot`.\n- Signed prerelease asset used for the Windows proof: `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-x64.exe`, release `v0.6.0-alpha.14`, digest `sha256:36405bd72e2c11bae0aa051b551b339982a66ffb59820d977ad9983dbf0b4d98`.\n\n## Still Draft\n- Need rerun full focused validation on current head after the final rebase.\n- Need rerun autoreview on current head.\n- Need refresh the Azure pond gateway to current head and reverify pairing + exec approvals with the signed Windows nodes.",
